# Involving Parent Volunteers and Older Students in Children's Activities

## Preparing for the Activity

* Discuss the activity with the parent volunteers and older students beforehand to ensure everyone is on the same page.
* Explain the goals and objectives of the activity and how it will benefit the children.
* Assign specific roles to the parent volunteers and older students, such as assisting with materials, providing guidance, or facilitating discussions.

## During the Activity

* Encourage the parent volunteers and older students to engage with the children and facilitate their learning.
* Provide opportunities for the children to take on leadership roles and make decisions.
* Encourage the parent volunteers and older students to ask open-ended questions and provide feedback to the children.

## After the Activity

* Debrief with the parent volunteers and older students to discuss what worked well and what didn't.
* Ask for their feedback and suggestions on how to improve the activity.
* Provide opportunities for the parent volunteers and older students to reflect on their experience and what they learned.

</OUTPUT_TEXT>
